<Author>YoPedro
<Content>Small, friendly, utilitarian hotel in good central location Hi all potential Barcelona travelers. I studied up on Barcelona hotels (on tripadvisor of course) and was relatively happy with my selection of the Onix Fira where I stayed for 4 nights in July while attending some business meetings. The Onix Fira is small and quite utilitarian. In other words, it's a nice clean simple hotel with a decent breakfast (free if you pay for it in your room fee) in a pretty good location. The hotel is within very short walking distance of the central train station, and also Placa Espana which has many col sights left over from various Olympic and world expo experiences.I was within about a 15 minute walk of an LDS church which was nice to find on Sunday morning. And also about 3 minutes walk from the Placa Espana metro/subway from where you can pretty much get anywhere else in Barcelona. The room was small by American standards, but did have a working TV, wireless internet connection, and locking safe. All you need when traveling on business. Though I suppose that if I was traveling with my wife I might want something a little fancier? or maybe not. I was able to get downtown in just a few minutes on the metro, so no point in staying in a hotel right downtown.There was still quite a bit of construction next door as they continue to renovate one of the two historic bull fighting rings in town into, yes, a shopping mall! 
<Date>Sep 18, 2008
