<Author>smiley_sheep
<Content>Could have been better I stayed at this hotel in September 2006 for 3 nights. My room was clean and spacious, I booked a double (two singles pushed together) as the prices were almost the same as if you booked a single. Lots of storage space as well as safe in room. The other great thing was that there were locks on your wardrobes so u could lock up all your belongings. Bathroom was large with a bath/shower. There was also free wi-fi which was great as it was a low cost option which enabled me to keep in contact with my family overseas!Now the downsides! My minibar was not working and was not repaired in all the time I was there - even though I reported it on the first day of arrival. Located on the end of a small street, facing a large construction site. Luckily they do not work on Saturday or Sunday so there was no noise or dust to contend with. I wouldn't recommend this hotel to traveller's who don't speak spanish because my very very limited Spanish and the staffs very very limited English made any form of communication difficult, even checking in! Location wise - it is alright. Right near the Placa Espanya and the montjuic area which has a number of tourist attractions there to visit. Ok hotel, but for the price I think I would find another hotel next time I return to Barcelona. 
<Date>Sep 21, 2006
