<Author>JoshNYC
<Content>Nice quiet place I've stayed here at least a dozen times, and find the place perfectly fine. There's absolutely nothing wrong with the Onix, but then again there's not much to the place either. It's on a quiet street in a residential neighborhood near Placa de Espanya and the train station, just behind a Miro-sculpted park. The rooms are comfortable, if a bit on the spartan side. But the elevators work great, the air conditioning is superb, and every room's got a tiny balcony on which to have a drink at the end of a hot Barcelona day. The lobby bar is great for a morning coffee or a quick snack, but I certainly wouldn't have a full meal there. Plenty of places within 20 minutes walk to get a fabulous lunch or dinner.You can walk to the Plaza Espanya subway station in under 5 minutes, and reasonably-priced taxis are almost always hovering nearby.Staff are pleasant and fairly knowledgeable. If you're going to need an early check-in, let them know ahead of time and they'll try to accommodate it. Sometimes they can't, and they'll be happy to store your luggage until there's a vacant room. All in all, this picky New Yorker was satisfied. If you're looking for luxury with frills and extra service, go to someplace like the Fira Palce or the Hotel Arts. But I like the Onix just fine. 
